# GCP IaaS Hardening Checklist

Mapped to CIS GCP Benchmark v1.3. Apply these controls immediately after provisioning any IaaS environment.

---

## IAM and Access Control

- [ ] **GCP-IAM-01** — Remove the Editor role from the default Compute Engine service account at project level  
  `gcloud projects remove-iam-policy-binding <PROJECT> --member="serviceAccount:<SA>" --role="roles/editor"`  
  *CIS: 1.4 | NIST: PR.AC-4*

- [ ] **GCP-IAM-02** — Create purpose-specific service accounts with only the permissions required per workload  
  *CIS: 1.5 | NIST: PR.AC-4*

- [ ] **GCP-IAM-03** — Disable the default service account where no service account is required on a VM  
  *CIS: 1.4 | NIST: PR.AC-4*

- [ ] **GCP-IAM-04** — Do not create or download service account keys; use Workload Identity Federation for external workloads  
  *CIS: 1.6 | NIST: PR.AC-1*

- [ ] **GCP-IAM-05** — Enforce MFA for all human user accounts in the organization  
  *CIS: 1.2 | NIST: PR.AC-1*

- [ ] **GCP-IAM-06** — Apply Org Policy constraint to restrict who can create service account keys  
  `constraints/iam.disableServiceAccountKeyCreation`  
  *CIS: 1.6 | NIST: PR.AC-4*

- [ ] **GCP-IAM-07** — Enable and configure Access Context Manager for context-aware access to GCP resources  
  *CIS: 1.15 | NIST: PR.AC-4*

